LAGOS – The Nigerian National Petroleum Corporation (NNPC), yesterday solicited the help of Indian companies for the Turn Around Maintenance of the nation’s ailing refineries. Dr. Maikanti Baru, Group Managing Director of the Corporation disclosed this when the Indian High Commissioner to Nigeria, His Excellency, Abhay Thakur, paid him a courtesy visit in his office. Baru had in his new-year statement disclosed that successive government didn’t do Turn-Around Maintenance on the nation’s refineries in the last 42years, adding that the current administration would expedite action to bring them alive. Baru, was quoted in a statement by the NNPC’s spokesman, Ndu Ughamadu, acknowledging the role of Indian companies in Nigeria as well as imploring them to extend their presence to the downstream sector of the Petroleum Industry to leverage on the enormous opportunities there. He assured the High Commissioner of NNPC’s commitment to further strengthen the existing relations between both countries in the energy sector Speaking earlier, the Indian High Commissioner, His Excellency, Thakur, commended Nigeria for its support to India in the area of energy security, stressing that Nigeria had been contributing significantly to India’s energy needs.